                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 836/86.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Ambassador <persName type="to">Dudley</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-01-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 15, 1908</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Bacon states that the department assumes that the decree signed by President
                    of Brazil on the 11th instant puts reduction of 20 per cent in force
                    retroactively as from January 1, and asks if this is correct.)</p>
            </div>
